components.name: Initialize Log Cleanup
components.description: Initialises the logcleanup workflow and fansout to parallel Bash workers.

upstream_policy.description: Runs at the start of the DAG without upstream dependencies.

components.name: Cleanup Airflow Logs
components.description: Executes parallel Bash commands to delete log files older than the configured age, removes empty subdirectories and parent directories, and coordinates workers via a lock file.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after the initialise task completes successfully.

connections.purpose: access optional child process log folder

batch_window.description: Batch window parameter name (e.g., ds, execution_date)

partitioning.description: Data partitioning strategy (e.g., daily, hourly, monthly)

depends_on_past.description: Whether execution depends on previous run success

max_log_age_in_days.description: Maximum age of logs to retain, provided via DAG run conf (maxLogAgeInDays)

enable_delete_child_log.description: Enable deletion of child process log directory (airflow_log_cleanup__enable_delete_child_log)

lock_file_path.description: Path to lock file for worker coordination

ALERT_EMAIL_ADDRESSES.description: Email addresses to send failure alerts

sources: Airflow core log files located in the BASE_LOG_FOLDER directory
Scheduler child process log files located in the CHILD_PROCESS_LOG_DIRECTORY (if enabled)
sinks: Deleted/cleaned log files and empty directories in the target log folders
Failure alert emails sent to addresses defined in ALERT_EMAIL_ADDRESSES
